    {
        "content": "<p>Aah -- the definition of <code>1</code> depends (in some sense) on whether k = 0 or k &gt; 0. Bumping up k to remove this ambiguity results in an even cooler error :-)</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">k</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Iic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">True</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">fin_cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hx</span>\n<span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">(kernel) declaration has metavariables '_example'</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">-/</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I think this means that the thing-that-happens-before-the-kernel thinks the proof is done; if you add <code>sorry</code> then you get the error saying that there are no goals to be solved. I don't know if the two errors are related or different.</p>",
